------------------------------------------------------------------------
Upstream attributions
------------------------------------------------------------------------

The bsc-invariants library is built on the following upstream work. Each
attribution carries the pinned version it currently targets; this file
is updated as pins move.

- Uniswap v3 — `Uniswap/v3-core`, GPL-2.0-or-later. PancakeSwap v3 is a
  1:1 fork of Uniswap v3's core math (`TickMath`, `SqrtPriceMath`,
  `SwapMath`, fee-growth accounting). The constants reproduced in
  `src/lib/TickMath.sol` (MIN_TICK, MAX_TICK, MIN_SQRT_RATIO,
  MAX_SQRT_RATIO) are facts about the protocol's address space, not
  copyrightable expression; the constants live in this repo with an
  attribution pointer rather than as a vendored file. If at M2 we
  vendor the GPL-licensed `TickMath.sol` source verbatim, this NOTICE
  + the file header will name it explicitly and the repo's license
  posture will be re-evaluated against GPL-2.0-or-later compatibility.

- PancakeSwap v3 — `pancakeswap/pancake-v3-contracts`, GPL-2.0-or-later
  for `projects/v3-core`. The reference contract in
  `src/PancakeV3FeeAccountingRef.sol` is a same-source twin minimal to
  the fee-growth + tick-bound invariants under test; it is NOT a fork
  of PancakeSwap's production source. The invariants tested are
  documented in `docs/invariants.md` with citations to the upstream
  v3 whitepaper (the canonical source for the fee-growth-only-grows
  property).

- CaliperForge hyperevm-safety — Apache-2.0. The Foundry config, the
  composite Foundry-setup GitHub Action, the path-gated CI pattern,
  and the planted-twin discipline are ported 1:1 from
  `experiments/hyperevm-safety/`. The `bsc-invariants` repo extends
  the discipline to BNB Smart Chain DeFi protocols (PancakeSwap v3 at
  M1; Venus + Stargate planned at M2 / M3).

- CaliperForge chimera-template-pack — Apache-2.0. Foundry + Recon
  Chimera + Echidna + Medusa scaffold. `bsc-invariants` reuses the
  composite-action pin pattern + the seeded-fuzz configuration. The
  full Chimera `Properties.sol` bundle is M2 work (not in the Week-1
  scaffold).

